---
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { formatDate } from "../utils/date";

const posts = (await getCollection("posts")).sort(
  (a, b) => new Date(b.data.date).valueOf() - new Date(a.data.date).valueOf()
);

const punchlines = [
  "It works on my machine.",
  "There are 2 hard things in CS: naming things, cache invalidation, and off-by-one errors.",
  "99 little bugs in the code, 99 little bugs...",
  "It's not a bug, it's an undocumented feature.",
  "Works in dev. Production is just a rumor.",
  "I don't always test my code, but when I do, I do it in production.",
  "Semicolons: the silent assassins.",
  "TODO: write a better TODO.",
  "git commit -m 'fix'",
  "git commit -m 'fix the fix'",
  "git commit -m 'final fix, I promise'",
  "Naming variables is 90% of my job. The other 90% is renaming them.",
  "Coffee: now compiling.",
  "404: motivation not found.",
  "It compiles, ship it.",
  "Regex: now you have two problems.",
  "I'd explain recursion, but I'd have to explain recursion.",
  "Schrödinger's deploy: it's broken and working until someone checks.",
  "The bug is always in the last place you look. Coincidence?",
  "AI wrote this. AI also broke this.",
  "rm -rf node_modules — the universal fix.",
  "Stack Overflow: where I copy-paste my career.",
  "console.log('here1')",
  "console.log('here2 - why??')",
  "Undefined is not a function. Neither am I, on Mondays.",
  "Merge conflict: the relationship test.",
  "CSS: where centering a div is a personal journey.",
  "It's always DNS.",
  "Friday deploys: a leap of faith.",
  "Tabs vs spaces: the war that never ends.",
  "I have 99 problems and they're all CORS.",
  "Cache invalidation: the other hard problem.",
  "One does not simply 'quick fix' on a Friday.",
  "I write code so I don't have to talk to people. The code talks back instead.",
  "Yes, I tested it. No, not on this branch.",
  "The cloud is just someone else's computer, crying.",
  "Infinite loop: my therapist calls it 'rumination'.",
  "It's not spaghetti code, it's job security.",
  "Comments: love letters to my future, confused self.",
  "Pull request: please don't read too closely.",
  "I refactored it. It's worse now, but cleaner.",
  "Async/await: because waiting is hard, apparently.",
  "Null pointer exception: my love life, summarized.",
  "I don't have bugs, I have surprise features.",
  "Reading documentation: a sign of weakness.",
  "Linter says no.",
  "Production is down. So is my will to live.",
  "I added a try/catch. Now everything fails silently. Progress.",
  "Variable named 'temp' since 2014.",
  "The function is called 'doStuff'. It does many stuffs.",
  "Hotfix: a fix applied while the building is on fire.",
  "I use Vim. Send help.",
  "Quantum computing: it's either working or not, and also both.",
  "npm install: now downloading the internet.",
  "Left-pad broke the internet once. Never forget.",
  "Code review: where 'nit:' means 'rewrite everything'.",
  "I commented out the test. It passes now.",
  "If it's stupid but it works, it's not stupid. It's still stupid, but it works.",
  "Debugging: being a detective in a crime movie where you're also the murderer.",
  "TypeScript: JavaScript with trust issues.",
  "Ctrl+Z: my favorite life feature.",
  "Refactoring at 4:58pm on a Friday: a bold choice.",
  "I named it 'final_v2_FINAL_real'.",
  "Singleton pattern: because one global variable wasn't enough.",
  "for (;;) {} — job security, line 1.",
  "Premature optimization: the root of all evil, and also my hobby.",
  "404: page exists, motivation doesn't.",
  "Deploying on a Friday is just chaos with extra steps.",
  "I read the error message. It lied to me.",
  "My code works. I don't know why. I'm scared to touch it.",
  "Endless meetings about agile, instead of being agile.",
  "Pair programming: two people, one bug, infinite blame.",
  "The demo gods demand sacrifice.",
  "Yes I'll write tests. After this one more feature.",
  "git blame: the modern detective story.",
  "I just need five more minutes... said every dev, forever.",
  "It's a feature, not a bug. Mostly because I can't fix it.",
  "I run on caffeine and unresolved merge conflicts.",
  "404: sleep not found.",
  "The build failed. The build is always right. The build is never right.",
  "Works on staging. Staging lied.",
  "I asked the AI. The AI also doesn't know.",
  "Every framework eventually reinvents jQuery.",
  "Documentation is a love letter you write to people who will never read it.",
  "I solved it with a global variable. I am not proud.",
  "The real bug was the assumptions we made along the way.",
  "My code is self-documenting. It documents chaos.",
  "There is no cloud, it's just fans and prayer.",
  "Two spaces? Four spaces? Tabs? I just want to go home.",
  "I deleted the cache. It fixed everything and nothing.",
  "JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(myProblems))",
  "Light theme by default — my eyes demanded it.",
  "Dark mode users will fight you. Respectfully.",
  "I wrote a script to automate this. Now I maintain the script.",
  "Version 1.0.0: optimism. Version 1.0.1: reality.",
  "I have a guy who builds websites. The guy is me. The guy is tired.",
  "Static site generators: because dynamic was too much commitment.",
  "Hardcoded values: today's quick fix, tomorrow's mystery.",
  "I trust this code about as much as I trust a CAPTCHA.",
  "Thanks for reading this far. Go touch grass.",
];
---
<Base title="lucabro.dev">
  <h1 class="page-title" id="punchline"></h1>
  <ul class="post-list">
    {posts.map((post) => {
      const formatted = formatDate(post.data.date);
      return (
        <li class="post-item">
          <a href={`/${post.id}`} class="post-link">
            <span class="post-title">{post.data.title}</span>
            <span class="post-meta">
              <time datetime={post.data.date}>{formatted}</time>
            </span>
          </a>
          {post.data.description && (
            <p class="post-excerpt">{post.data.description}</p>
          )}
        </li>
      );
    })}
  </ul>
</Base>

<script define:vars={{ punchlines }}>
  const el = document.getElementById("punchline");
  el.textContent = punchlines[Math.floor(Math.random() * punchlines.length)];
</script>

<style>
  .page-title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .post-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }

  .post-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .post-title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .post-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .post-excerpt {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .post-link:hover .post-title {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .post-link:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
  }
</style>
